1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:02,110
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,110 --> 00:00:03,780
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:05,810 --> 00:00:06,980
Aren't you going to eat lunch?

4
00:00:07,050 --> 00:00:09,680
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

5
00:00:09,750 --> 00:00:11,650
Where did he go?
He skipped breakfast, too.

6
00:00:19,020 --> 00:00:20,230
Have a seat, Grandpa.

7
00:00:22,160 --> 00:00:23,400
Are you protesting or something?

8
00:00:28,770 --> 00:00:30,140
Do my words mean nothing to you?

9
00:00:30,700 --> 00:00:33,640
Have you no shame, acting like this
in front of your nephew? Pathetic.

10
00:00:33,810 --> 00:00:37,140
Fine, I'm pathetic. No wonder
you voted for amazing Jeong Han.

11
00:00:39,680 --> 00:00:40,850
Good grief.

12
00:00:41,250 --> 00:00:43,110
What does he expect to accomplish
by acting like that?

13
00:00:46,890 --> 00:00:48,050
Where did everyone go?

14
00:00:48,890 --> 00:00:51,460
- What about your aunt?
- I don't know either.

15
00:00:51,990 --> 00:00:53,990
She just told me to make sure
you two had lunch.

16
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:01,730
Hey. It's not like he's the only one
in the world selling that bag.

17
00:01:02,470 --> 00:01:05,140
Auntie, I'm telling you,
it's a limited-edition Cabanel.

18
00:01:05,470 --> 00:01:08,410
Exactly. How many people
do you think would be selling one?

19
00:01:09,510 --> 00:01:13,750
I'm so glad I added it
to my watchlist on the resale app.

20
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:15,880
What am I going to do?

21
00:01:16,450 --> 00:01:17,780
Will I be able to track him down?

22
00:01:18,980 --> 00:01:22,420
- What if he sees me and runs?
- Don't worry, Auntie.

23
00:01:22,950 --> 00:01:25,290
Because I'll be the bait.

24
00:01:26,490 --> 00:01:29,760
Dong Suk, I can run 100m
in 15.2 seconds.

25
00:01:29,860 --> 00:01:31,760
And I'm wearing sneakers today.

26
00:01:42,540 --> 00:01:44,580
Hey, Woo Jae, it's Eun Bin.

27
00:01:45,340 --> 00:01:49,280
I wanted to keep my promise, even if
it were the end of the world, but...

28
00:01:49,610 --> 00:01:53,490
I'm having a massive dopamine rush,
and my heart's going into overdrive.

29
00:01:53,950 --> 00:01:56,550
Okay. I was just about
to call you, actually.

30
00:01:57,390 --> 00:01:58,760
Something's come up on my end, too.

31
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,360
Yes.

32
00:02:00,860 --> 00:02:02,330
Okay, let's talk later.

33
00:02:10,300 --> 00:02:11,300
But...

34
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:14,840
shouldn't Dae Han come with us, too?

35
00:02:17,180 --> 00:02:18,780
I'm worried
she might be with some guy.

36
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:20,850
Dae Han...

37
00:02:22,480 --> 00:02:23,750
I don't want him...

38
00:02:24,550 --> 00:02:25,950
to see that.

39
00:02:35,090 --> 00:02:38,660
Pharmacy's closed. Where's Mom?
She isn't answering her phone.

40
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:42,200
Nurse Oh, do you know anything?

41
00:02:42,770 --> 00:02:44,370
You know everything
that goes on around here.

42
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:46,000
That's just it.

43
00:02:46,300 --> 00:02:47,910
I'm surprised
there's something I don't know.

44
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:51,980
I feel like
I'm the only one in the family...

45
00:02:51,980 --> 00:02:53,980
who doesn't know what's going on.

46
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:58,550
Then it must be about me.
So why am I in the dark?

47
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:00,750
About you? What?
Is something going on with you?

48
00:03:01,320 --> 00:03:02,350
Nothing.

49
00:03:03,350 --> 00:03:07,860
Is there a family group chat
that doesn't include me?

50
00:03:08,090 --> 00:03:09,230
You never know.

51
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:11,300
We're not that mean.

52
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:14,230
But it's so weird.

53
00:03:14,770 --> 00:03:19,070
I have this gut feeling
that something's going on.

54
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:22,110
Then it's nothing.
You have the worst intuition.

55
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:23,640
The worst intuition?

56
00:03:25,010 --> 00:03:26,480
I guess my intuition
isn't very good after all.

57
00:03:29,910 --> 00:03:31,380
Oh, this way.

58
00:03:36,650 --> 00:03:37,690
It's that way.

59
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:39,760
Ganghwa Mart Entrance.

60
00:03:41,190 --> 00:03:44,300
I'll go meet him.
You two hide, then grab him.

61
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,360
Got it?

62
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:47,730
Where on earth are we?

63
00:03:48,300 --> 00:03:50,340
What's he doing
in a completely random neighborhood?

64
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:53,040
Let's go, Dong Suk.

65
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:56,170
I'm coming for you, my Cabanel!

66
00:03:58,010 --> 00:03:59,010
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

67
00:03:59,010 --> 00:04:00,610
Honey, just a second.

68
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,480
Hey, that guy.

69
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,650
Oh, my. Wait.

70
00:04:07,650 --> 00:04:09,250
Isn't he the son-in-law
from the Korean medicine clinic?

71
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,630
- Honey, wait just a second.
- Okay.

72
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:15,590
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

73
00:04:15,660 --> 00:04:17,230
- Mom, Grandma.
- I can't believe it.

74
00:04:17,960 --> 00:04:18,960
What is it?

75
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,100
Look.

76
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:27,940
- This is it, right?
- Dong Suk, over here!

77
00:04:29,410 --> 00:04:31,540
- What now?
- If you go this way...

78
00:04:31,610 --> 00:04:32,610
Where is this place?

79
00:04:34,280 --> 00:04:36,350
I'll hold them off. You go first.

80
00:04:38,020 --> 00:04:40,220
Grandma, let's go. Hurry.

81
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:47,830
My gosh!

82
00:04:49,230 --> 00:04:50,500
Your hands must be freezing.

83
00:04:55,430 --> 00:04:56,530
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

84
00:05:00,300 --> 00:05:01,340
My mother-in-law...

85
00:05:05,140 --> 00:05:06,610
Wait...

86
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:08,380
Where are you going?

87
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:10,010
I'll get him.

88
00:05:10,980 --> 00:05:12,720
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

89
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:17,360
Hello.

90
00:05:20,690 --> 00:05:22,160
We just turn here.

91
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,700
- I don't think this is it.
- My gosh!

92
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:28,400
- Fancy seeing you here.
- Mother!

93
00:05:28,470 --> 00:05:31,000
Have you lost your mind?
Why are you calling her "Mother?"

94
00:05:33,840 --> 00:05:36,310
Doctor, what brings you here?

95
00:05:38,380 --> 00:05:40,110
The public health center here...

96
00:05:40,410 --> 00:05:43,110
asked me to run
a mental health program.

97
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:48,420
That's so admirable.
Mother, it's good to see you here!

98
00:05:50,090 --> 00:05:52,590
We have some business to attend to,
so we'll get going.

99
00:05:52,890 --> 00:05:53,890
And where...

100
00:05:54,890 --> 00:05:56,260
might you be going?

101
00:05:56,630 --> 00:05:57,630
Excuse me?

102
00:06:01,070 --> 00:06:03,700
We're just looking for someone.

103
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:07,910
I see.

104
00:06:08,770 --> 00:06:12,940
You're looking for someone.

105
00:06:20,490 --> 00:06:22,090
Then, go ahead.

106
00:06:22,890 --> 00:06:23,890
I'll be on my way as well.

107
00:06:25,190 --> 00:06:27,430
See you again soon, Mother.

108
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:35,930
What is her deal? Let's go, hurry.

109
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:40,140
- Let's go.
- She's so elegant, unlike someone.

110
00:06:48,650 --> 00:06:49,650
Shoot...

111
00:06:58,720 --> 00:07:01,260
Darn it. Unbelievable.

112
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,060
Stay back. Don't follow me.

113
00:07:06,300 --> 00:07:07,300
Stop right there.

114
00:07:21,110 --> 00:07:22,250
Get away from me.

115
00:07:23,510 --> 00:07:24,680
Get lost!

116
00:07:24,980 --> 00:07:27,220
Get lost? You've got nowhere to go.

117
00:07:29,790 --> 00:07:31,820
If you don't want your family
to find out,

118
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:35,090
- just stay put.
- Darn it.

119
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:43,370
Yes, Mom.

120
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:44,700
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

121
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:46,200
When I call you later,

122
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,940
bring him to that place
we saw earlier.

123
00:07:49,170 --> 00:07:51,640
(Hui Gyeong Hair Salon)

124
00:07:56,650 --> 00:07:57,680
Cabanel?

125
00:08:00,650 --> 00:08:01,650
Cabanel.

126
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:03,390
- What's that?
- What?

127
00:08:04,760 --> 00:08:05,860
What the...

128
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:10,900
(Ganghwa Mart Entrance)

129
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:17,570
It's past the meeting time.
Why hasn't anyone shown up?

130
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:21,010
Maybe someone else
offered a higher price?

131
00:08:22,770 --> 00:08:24,110
Darn it...

132
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:45,700
(Cabanel)

133
00:09:12,090 --> 00:09:14,830
By any chance, is Dae Han here, too?

134
00:09:15,990 --> 00:09:17,860
Thank goodness
he didn't come with us.

135
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:21,670
How long has this been going on?

136
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:25,300
Just how long
have you been planning this?

137
00:09:27,870 --> 00:09:29,740
It's been about three years.

138
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:34,610
- Three years?
- Yes. While visiting you,

139
00:09:34,680 --> 00:09:36,980
we started running into each other.

140
00:09:38,750 --> 00:09:39,920
Wait, so...

141
00:09:40,920 --> 00:09:43,620
is that why you agreed so quickly
when I suggested we live together?

142
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:47,430
Yes. I thought I'd see him more...

143
00:09:47,490 --> 00:09:50,090
He's a married man!
The head of another household,

144
00:09:50,190 --> 00:09:51,760
and a father with a child!

145
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:55,700
But they say love knows no bounds.

146
00:10:07,650 --> 00:10:10,820
I bet someone tried to scam us
with a fake bag.

147
00:10:11,820 --> 00:10:13,750
You think he saw us and ran off?

148
00:10:13,850 --> 00:10:17,920
No. Ji Hu's dad has no connection
to this neighborhood.

149
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:22,690
That girl always jumps the gun...
What a waste of time.

150
00:10:25,100 --> 00:10:29,870
Hey, you'll never guess who I saw.
It was your mom! Isn't that crazy?

151
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:31,770
I think we're totally meant to be.

152
00:10:34,910 --> 00:10:35,940
Right.

153
00:10:37,140 --> 00:10:40,040
Oh, I see.

154
00:10:40,810 --> 00:10:44,680
Okay. Let's talk later.
All right, bye.

155
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:56,930
For a man with a wife and child,
is this how you should be acting?

156
00:10:57,800 --> 00:11:01,530
If you wanted to be with her,
you should've divorced your wife.

157
00:11:02,100 --> 00:11:03,500
If you just run off like this,

158
00:11:03,900 --> 00:11:07,640
your family is left to wait forever
without ever knowing why.

159
00:11:08,410 --> 00:11:10,540
How can you be so irresponsible?

160
00:11:12,540 --> 00:11:15,510
My mother-in-law is talking
about herself.

161
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:18,750
Look, Hui Gyeong.

162
00:11:19,250 --> 00:11:23,290
You of all people know the pain
our family has lived with,

163
00:11:24,290 --> 00:11:26,290
so how could you do this to us?

164
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:27,760
Us?

165
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:31,160
There you go again,
ganging up on me.

166
00:11:32,730 --> 00:11:36,270
- What?
- You two always take the same side.

167
00:11:36,770 --> 00:11:39,600
You're the doctor she's so proud of,
and she's a pharmacist.

168
00:11:40,040 --> 00:11:43,210
That's why I always felt
singled out by you, Mother.

169
00:11:43,410 --> 00:11:44,410
What...

170
00:11:45,040 --> 00:11:47,410
Are you saying
I discriminated against you?

171
00:11:47,480 --> 00:11:49,350
It's true! You looked down on me
because I'm an orphan,

172
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:50,820
and you always favored her over me.

173
00:11:51,850 --> 00:11:52,920
Have you forgotten?

174
00:11:53,620 --> 00:11:56,720
I'm an orphan, too.
My parents passed away,

175
00:11:56,790 --> 00:11:58,820
and I was raised by my grandmother
before I married into this family.

176
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:00,790
Right.

177
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:03,360
- That's right.
- So?

178
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:06,260
You really think
Mother played favorites?

179
00:12:06,660 --> 00:12:08,000
What have you ever done?

180
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:10,900
Have you ever lifted a finger
since you got married?

181
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:15,110
Have you ever once cleaned
your own room or bathroom?

182
00:12:15,440 --> 00:12:19,940
She supported your education,
and this is the scheme you cook up?

183
00:12:20,310 --> 00:12:24,850
- What? You felt singled out?
- You never did housework either!

184
00:12:24,920 --> 00:12:26,280
And did I have an affair?

185
00:12:26,350 --> 00:12:30,220
You and your husband always fight.
You just pretend to be happy on TV.

186
00:12:30,590 --> 00:12:33,820
I'm better off choosing love
than living a lie like you.

187
00:12:34,190 --> 00:12:38,700
How dare you cheat and talk of love
in front of your mother-in-law?

188
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:42,530
- She is no longer my mother-in-law.
- Hey!

189
00:12:42,930 --> 00:12:45,840
Snap out of it! Are you divorced?

190
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:49,010
You're an adulteress who cheated
on her husband behind his back.

191
00:12:49,070 --> 00:12:51,080
And a homewrecker
who destroyed another family!

192
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:56,050
You're really scary. You look like
you're going to hit me.

193
00:13:09,290 --> 00:13:12,730
Don't delude yourself into thinking
he's going to love you forever.

194
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:17,370
Someone who's cheated once
is much more likely to do it again.

195
00:13:18,340 --> 00:13:19,670
You don't know
what you're talking about.

196
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:24,310
He's not like that.
He said he had never cheated before.

197
00:13:24,540 --> 00:13:26,910
We truly love each other.

198
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:30,950
He might be sweet to you now,
caught in the thrill of the affair,

199
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:35,320
but will he be responsible
when he's married with a child?

200
00:13:36,750 --> 00:13:39,890
Darling. You're not going to
abandon me, are you?

201
00:13:40,060 --> 00:13:41,930
No, of course not. Never.

202
00:13:43,260 --> 00:13:45,100
You will both go back to your homes.

203
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:46,960
Get your divorces,
then you can be together.

204
00:13:49,970 --> 00:13:53,400
- What if my husband won't agree?
- I'll make him.

205
00:13:54,070 --> 00:13:57,910
Do as I say, or you'll have to hide.
Otherwise, you both...

206
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:01,450
will end up in court
on theft charges.

207
00:14:03,710 --> 00:14:04,820
What happened here today...

208
00:14:05,620 --> 00:14:07,220
stays between us.

209
00:14:07,920 --> 00:14:10,520
Consider it a final courtesy...

210
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,390
to the people
who were once your family.

211
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:15,260
Yes, I understand.

212
00:14:16,190 --> 00:14:17,260
In that case...

213
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:20,600
So I can keep the security deposit
and the savings?

214
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:24,640
If you let me keep it,
I'll agree to a clean divorce.

215
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,270
If you don't,

216
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:29,570
I'll tell everyone in town
that I ran off with him.

217
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:31,410
You really are...

218
00:14:31,810 --> 00:14:34,310
a terribly conniving person,
aren't you?

219
00:14:42,150 --> 00:14:44,920
(Taehan)

220
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:50,460
I haven't seen the Director around.
Did he go eat somewhere else?

221
00:14:51,460 --> 00:14:53,460
He's probably busy with marketing.

222
00:14:53,960 --> 00:14:55,900
You haven't seen him
since we got back, have you?

223
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:58,370
What? No.

224
00:14:59,970 --> 00:15:02,170
It's good to see you again,
Yang Hyun Bin.

225
00:15:09,410 --> 00:15:12,120
I've missed you, Gong Ju Ah.

226
00:15:23,890 --> 00:15:25,060
Hold on!

227
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:31,870
Yes. I'm sorry. Sorry about that.

228
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:42,850
Excuse me, I'm sorry.

229
00:16:00,730 --> 00:16:02,530
All right, Director.
I'll be heading out.

230
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:03,830
Okay.

231
00:16:07,470 --> 00:16:08,540
Hey, have you been busy?

232
00:16:09,170 --> 00:16:11,010
Oh, we're at the office...
What was I thinking?

233
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:12,610
Have you been busy, sir?

234
00:16:14,880 --> 00:16:17,920
Yes. I just came from a meeting
with the marketing team.

235
00:16:18,350 --> 00:16:19,720
I see.

236
00:16:24,790 --> 00:16:26,190
I should get going.

237
00:16:26,260 --> 00:16:29,390
You were thrown off by Eun Bin
yesterday, right?

238
00:16:29,930 --> 00:16:33,730
- The double in-laws part?
- Yes, that "sister-in-law" thing.

239
00:16:34,770 --> 00:16:37,200
It's fine.
I'm sure she was just joking.

240
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:38,800
Yes, probably.

241
00:16:41,040 --> 00:16:44,680
I should really get going.
I'm busy with the contest deadline.

242
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:46,880
Right, go ahead.
Good luck with your work.

243
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:48,750
You too, Director.

244
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,150
So Hye. Working on the presentation
for the contest?

245
00:17:21,350 --> 00:17:24,250
Yes, I am, but...

246
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:28,220
it's my first time presenting,
so I'm really nervous.

247
00:17:28,690 --> 00:17:31,560
I'll help. Just put together a draft
of the presentation for me.

248
00:17:32,020 --> 00:17:33,020
That's amazing!

249
00:17:34,490 --> 00:17:38,100
Seriously, Ms. Gong,
you're an absolute lifesaver.

250
00:17:39,760 --> 00:17:41,630
Okay, you can let go.

251
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:45,000
- Gong Ju Ah.
- Yes?

252
00:17:45,070 --> 00:17:46,200
The Vice President wants to see you.

253
00:17:47,070 --> 00:17:48,110
Okay.

254
00:17:49,940 --> 00:17:52,180
I called you here with a request
for the Design Office.

255
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:56,680
For the next season, we will launch
Kim So Hye's design as its own line,

256
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:59,350
as part of a strategy
to elevate our brand image.

257
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:01,550
Elevating the brand? I love it!

258
00:18:02,050 --> 00:18:06,920
They've requested a premium spot
at Hyegyeong Department Store.

259
00:18:07,290 --> 00:18:10,990
But they take just two brands
a season in that section,

260
00:18:11,060 --> 00:18:12,700
so it's not going to be easy.

261
00:18:13,230 --> 00:18:15,630
The waiting list to get in
must be totally full too, Director.

262
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:19,240
You're underestimating Pacu Nacho.
He makes the impossible possible.

263
00:18:19,670 --> 00:18:22,940
I skipped the official channels
and got a meeting with their buyer.

264
00:18:23,310 --> 00:18:27,540
So we need to rush
to get a proposal ready by Monday.

265
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,310
Any volunteers to help out?

266
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:33,020
When it comes to proposals,
our Gong Ju Ah is the expert.

267
00:18:33,950 --> 00:18:36,850
Then Ju Ah can do it.
Go to Pacu Nacho's office.

268
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:38,560
Wait, hold on.

269
00:18:38,620 --> 00:18:42,790
But I already promised to help
So Hye with her presentation.

270
00:18:42,860 --> 00:18:46,100
Oh, then I guess
Ms. Gong isn't available.

271
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:48,900
Hey, it's all part
of the same project.

272
00:18:49,170 --> 00:18:51,640
You can just use the proposal
for the presentation materials.

273
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:55,270
- That's not how it works.
- Oh, come on, you two.

274
00:18:55,640 --> 00:18:57,770
Everyone here knows you two
were each other's first loves.

275
00:18:59,510 --> 00:19:02,810
I'm pairing you for work, so maybe
you can start a romance here, okay?

276
00:19:03,180 --> 00:19:07,920
Vice President, a comment like that
qualifies as workplace coercion...

277
00:19:07,990 --> 00:19:09,320
and is grounds
for disciplinary action.

278
00:19:09,590 --> 00:19:10,620
That's right.

279
00:19:11,890 --> 00:19:12,920
Is that so, Mr. Park?

280
00:19:13,320 --> 00:19:14,930
Coercion?
What are you talking about?

281
00:19:15,790 --> 00:19:16,830
I'd call it an employee perk.

282
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:20,930
- You're unbelievable.
- Let's keep this professional.

283
00:19:21,370 --> 00:19:23,370
And let me make one thing
perfectly clear.

284
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:26,140
Gong Ju Ah and I are just friends.

285
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,070
- Friends?
- Friends?

286
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:33,680
Yes. We're just friends.

287
00:19:42,590 --> 00:19:45,920
Friends? As if. He said
he still had feelings for you.

288
00:19:46,160 --> 00:19:48,060
That was just the alcohol talking.

289
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:52,560
Hey! Then why the long face?
Are you sure you're just friends?

290
00:19:52,830 --> 00:19:55,170
I'm not disappointed! And yes,
we're definitely just friends.

291
00:19:56,570 --> 00:19:57,940
"Just friends?" Whatever.

292
00:19:58,270 --> 00:19:59,870
Men and women
can't be "just friends."

293
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,440
Hey, then what does that make us?

294
00:20:02,710 --> 00:20:04,740
That's different.

295
00:20:05,040 --> 00:20:07,510
It's because Pacu Nacho
likes Gong Ju Ah.

296
00:20:07,780 --> 00:20:10,050
Fine. Okay? I like her. Happy now?

297
00:20:10,410 --> 00:20:11,880
So what am I supposed
to do about it?

298
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:15,290
I have to go back in a year,
and our families are sworn enemies.

299
00:20:15,620 --> 00:20:17,520
Oh, so you're "just friends"
because you have no other choice.

300
00:20:17,590 --> 00:20:20,090
Right. So just drop it.

301
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:23,790
Fine, I get it. I'll be watching.

302
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,900
(Proposal:
Background and Objectives)

303
00:20:35,640 --> 00:20:36,740
So, what do you think?

304
00:20:37,010 --> 00:20:39,280
I felt we needed a more aggressive
marketing approach,

305
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:42,050
so I just whipped up
a draft on my own.

306
00:20:42,310 --> 00:20:44,310
Hush, you're distracting me.

307
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:45,950
Right.

308
00:20:48,720 --> 00:20:51,760
Hey, you're pretty blunt
with your director.

309
00:20:52,320 --> 00:20:54,520
That's a pretty high-handed thing
to say.

310
00:20:55,160 --> 00:20:56,230
Point taken.

311
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,140
So what don't you like?

312
00:21:07,570 --> 00:21:11,070
The proposal itself is a nice change
from the usual.

313
00:21:11,140 --> 00:21:15,180
It's unique and impressive.
It's just that the slogan is...

314
00:21:16,110 --> 00:21:17,110
It's kind of lame.

315
00:21:19,750 --> 00:21:22,490
"Return
to our original luxurious vibe,"

316
00:21:22,550 --> 00:21:25,390
"classic yet experimental."

317
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,720
That's the kind of feeling
I was hoping for.

318
00:21:28,690 --> 00:21:32,030
Like "Return to Origin?"

319
00:21:34,560 --> 00:21:37,500
To get back to the essence of FG...

320
00:21:38,100 --> 00:21:39,800
How about "Return to FG?"

321
00:21:41,470 --> 00:21:46,040
- Do you like that one?
- Yes. You catch on quick.

322
00:21:46,740 --> 00:21:49,710
Excellent. Very good job,
Yang Hyun Bin.

323
00:21:49,780 --> 00:21:53,650
Are you going to keep treating me
like that little middle schooler?

324
00:21:53,780 --> 00:21:57,550
I'm so proud. You've grown up.
I'm impressed.

325
00:21:58,620 --> 00:22:02,030
- Okay, "Return to FG," it is.
- Okay.

326
00:22:04,290 --> 00:22:07,360
Being back in this room
after so long,

327
00:22:07,830 --> 00:22:10,300
it reminds me of my first day here.

328
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:13,700
I even had a nightmare that night.

329
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:17,070
Really? I thought it was great.

330
00:22:17,410 --> 00:22:20,880
Of course, you did.
You knew who I was.

331
00:22:21,480 --> 00:22:25,850
You're so petty and sly.
Knowing full well who I was.

332
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:27,080
You enjoyed it, didn't you?

333
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,650
You were unbelievably clueless.

334
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:30,990
I told you my name,
and you still had no idea.

335
00:22:31,050 --> 00:22:33,460
So you basically tricked me.

336
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:37,190
Guilty as charged.
Let's get back to work.

337
00:22:38,630 --> 00:22:39,630
Fine.

338
00:22:40,030 --> 00:22:43,030
Even if we work all night,
I doubt we can finish by Monday.

339
00:22:44,000 --> 00:22:45,470
All right, then.

340
00:22:48,440 --> 00:22:51,210
"Return to FG."

341
00:22:53,810 --> 00:22:54,910
Not bad.

342
00:22:56,650 --> 00:23:00,120
Just check if you're for or against
opening the night market.

343
00:23:02,550 --> 00:23:06,320
If we open a night market,
it'll bring more youth, right?

344
00:23:06,660 --> 00:23:08,160
Yes, I suppose so.

345
00:23:09,390 --> 00:23:13,360
I heard Gopyeong Market became
a tourist hot spot by opening one.

346
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,630
- I hope it turns out well.
- Yes, well...

347
00:23:20,700 --> 00:23:21,940
Darn it.

348
00:23:23,010 --> 00:23:24,340
How am I supposed
to get all this done?

349
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:26,340
That jerk...

350
00:23:27,940 --> 00:23:28,950
But wait.

351
00:23:29,850 --> 00:23:32,250
If the night market opens,
doesn't that mean more work for me?

352
00:23:32,820 --> 00:23:33,850
Wait a second.

353
00:23:36,250 --> 00:23:37,950
(Onjeong Night Market Petition:
For or against)

354
00:23:43,030 --> 00:23:45,060
(Onjeong Market
Merchants' Association)

355
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:49,570
I've collected all the petitions
for and against the night market.

356
00:23:50,270 --> 00:23:52,270
- Already?
- Yes, already.

357
00:23:53,140 --> 00:23:54,940
Man, a lot of people are against it.

358
00:23:56,670 --> 00:23:57,910
Really? Why?

359
00:23:58,680 --> 00:24:02,480
They worry night customers will mean
their daytime business will suffer,

360
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:04,550
and they'll be stuck
with all the trash and noise.

361
00:24:04,550 --> 00:24:06,250
It's obvious
it'll mean more work for them.

362
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:09,050
That's what they said.

363
00:24:09,050 --> 00:24:10,890
You have no idea how hard I worked
to convince them after all that.

364
00:24:12,260 --> 00:24:13,920
All right, I get it.

365
00:24:15,290 --> 00:24:16,560
I can't make it this weekend.

366
00:24:16,990 --> 00:24:17,990
Why not?

367
00:24:17,990 --> 00:24:21,830
Hey, I'm going golfing with
City Councilor Hwang this Sunday.

368
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,970
Sunday? Then what about tomorrow?

369
00:24:25,040 --> 00:24:27,340
Tomorrow, I have to hit the range
and warm up.

370
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:30,440
Like this. Wow, nice shot!

371
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:34,380
Hey. If you want
to get that nomination,

372
00:24:34,510 --> 00:24:39,150
don't show off. Just go easy on him.
If you play too well without tact,

373
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:42,490
you'll fall out of his favor.
Kiss that nomination goodbye.

374
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:46,060
Are you telling me
you're worried about me?

375
00:24:50,460 --> 00:24:51,460
Get going.

376
00:24:52,860 --> 00:24:53,860
Hello?

377
00:24:54,900 --> 00:24:56,100
The Councilor's Office?

378
00:24:57,570 --> 00:24:59,340
You mean... Mr. Hwang?

379
00:25:00,570 --> 00:25:02,370
- Get going.
- What? Yes.

380
00:25:03,740 --> 00:25:05,640
Yes, but may I ask
what this is about?

381
00:25:07,210 --> 00:25:08,280
Right now?

382
00:25:09,180 --> 00:25:11,080
Yes, I'm available.

383
00:25:12,550 --> 00:25:14,280
Yes, I know the place. Okay.

384
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:18,860
Why is he going in there?

385
00:25:31,570 --> 00:25:33,300
Hello, sir.

386
00:25:33,670 --> 00:25:36,040
- It's a pleasure to meet you.
- Hello, Mr. Hwang.

387
00:25:36,540 --> 00:25:37,770
I hear you do a lot of good work.

388
00:25:37,970 --> 00:25:39,940
Why is Councilor Hwang
meeting with that jerk?

389
00:25:40,110 --> 00:25:41,440
Let's talk more inside.

390
00:25:41,910 --> 00:25:43,050
Of course.

391
00:25:48,620 --> 00:25:49,690
What the...

392
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:52,760
Councilor Hwang?

393
00:25:53,820 --> 00:25:55,130
Councilor Hwang?
Our district's big shot?

394
00:25:55,730 --> 00:25:56,730
Yes.

395
00:25:57,390 --> 00:25:58,460
So, what did he want?

396
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:01,200
He's recruiting
for the city council.

397
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,730
He asked if I'd be interested.

398
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:05,470
That makes sense.
You're respected in the community.

399
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,700
Also, you're talented
and so down-to-earth.

400
00:26:08,040 --> 00:26:12,040
I guess his parents were my patients
at one point.

401
00:26:12,340 --> 00:26:13,410
I wonder who they are.

402
00:26:13,840 --> 00:26:15,880
So, you're not interested?

403
00:26:16,350 --> 00:26:18,250
You've talked about
public health policy before.

404
00:26:18,450 --> 00:26:22,050
No. If your sister-in-law finds out,
I'm a dead man.

405
00:26:22,250 --> 00:26:23,690
Gosh, seriously.

406
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:26,720
Hey, by the way...

407
00:26:27,020 --> 00:26:29,030
Hasn't Bucket been trying
to get in good with him?

408
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:31,190
If he finds out you met with him,
he's going to flip out.

409
00:26:32,130 --> 00:26:35,230
That's a given. Oh, brother.

410
00:26:36,370 --> 00:26:38,070
Dr. Gong is quite the sly one,
isn't he?

411
00:26:39,100 --> 00:26:42,040
Don't tell me he's actually aiming
to run for city council.

412
00:26:43,140 --> 00:26:44,470
That jerk's real target is me.

413
00:26:45,510 --> 00:26:47,540
His goal has always been
to take whatever I want.

414
00:26:48,180 --> 00:26:50,710
Honey, try not to let it get to you.

415
00:26:51,450 --> 00:26:54,780
He won over my father,
and now he's after Mr. Hwang.

416
00:26:54,850 --> 00:26:56,390
How can I not let it get to me?

417
00:26:56,690 --> 00:26:58,620
But we have that round of golf,
remember?

418
00:26:58,990 --> 00:27:02,160
I'll be there all day,
and I'll do my best to win him over.

419
00:27:04,190 --> 00:27:08,030
But where have you been?
You didn't even make me lunch.

420
00:27:09,400 --> 00:27:12,240
Did you have a nice, cozy lunch
with your father?

421
00:27:12,700 --> 00:27:17,170
- What father? I don't have one.
- Honey, come on, let it go.

422
00:27:17,540 --> 00:27:19,840
Don't dodge the question.
I'm asking where you went.

423
00:27:19,910 --> 00:27:23,080
What? You didn't track my phone?

424
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:24,810
I guess the spark is gone.

425
00:27:24,950 --> 00:27:27,550
It's not that the spark is gone.
It's that I trust you now.

426
00:27:28,520 --> 00:27:30,390
I have to admit
I like the sound of that more.

427
00:27:30,450 --> 00:27:33,690
I just went shopping
with your sister and Eun Bin.

428
00:27:46,970 --> 00:27:49,310
- Get out. Now.
- Look.

429
00:27:49,770 --> 00:27:51,780
Please, just tell Dae Han
to come out here.

430
00:27:52,640 --> 00:27:54,140
I don't want to go in that house.

431
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,120
Keep your promise.

432
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:04,450
Tell him who your affair was with,
and I'll make you pay.

433
00:28:04,650 --> 00:28:07,060
How many times must I tell you?
I get it, okay?

434
00:28:08,260 --> 00:28:09,330
So...

435
00:28:10,130 --> 00:28:11,290
the money is mine, right?

436
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:25,980
You're back?

437
00:28:26,510 --> 00:28:30,010
My gosh,
where is everyone coming from?

438
00:28:30,610 --> 00:28:31,980
Dae Han, go out there.

439
00:28:32,850 --> 00:28:33,880
Hui Gyeong's here.

440
00:28:36,450 --> 00:28:39,060
What? Hey... What's with him?

441
00:28:39,390 --> 00:28:41,990
What's going on?
Did something happen to her aunt?

442
00:28:42,890 --> 00:28:44,390
I'll explain.

443
00:28:45,060 --> 00:28:46,860
Woo Jae, take Grandma inside.

444
00:28:52,200 --> 00:28:54,370
Why? What is it? What's going on?

445
00:28:56,170 --> 00:28:59,580
Your sister-in-law
is seeing another man.

446
00:29:00,310 --> 00:29:02,580
The two of them
are getting a divorce.

447
00:29:02,850 --> 00:29:03,880
What?

448
00:29:04,810 --> 00:29:07,750
What the... Who is this guy?

449
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:09,790
We don't know who he is either.

450
00:29:12,060 --> 00:29:14,420
Go comfort your brother. Okay?

451
00:29:18,530 --> 00:29:19,530
Unbelievable...

452
00:29:34,840 --> 00:29:37,880
You're furious with me, aren't you?

453
00:29:38,950 --> 00:29:39,950
I was just curious.

454
00:29:40,950 --> 00:29:42,120
About why you did it.

455
00:29:44,450 --> 00:29:48,760
You knew how my father left us,
and because of that,

456
00:29:49,230 --> 00:29:52,530
you knew how much pain
our family went through.

457
00:29:52,730 --> 00:29:54,460
And I... Honey...

458
00:29:56,400 --> 00:30:00,340
I took such good care of you
and cherished you so much,

459
00:30:01,170 --> 00:30:03,240
and I loved you so much.

460
00:30:03,670 --> 00:30:08,110
How could you do this to me?
What did I do wrong? I want to know.

461
00:30:08,650 --> 00:30:11,110
You didn't do anything wrong to me.

462
00:30:12,150 --> 00:30:13,150
Then...

463
00:30:14,920 --> 00:30:16,420
Why did you do it?

464
00:30:16,820 --> 00:30:18,050
I just...

465
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:22,130
I fell in love. Love...

466
00:30:22,390 --> 00:30:24,160
isn't a crime, you know.

467
00:30:40,940 --> 00:30:42,010
Who is it?

468
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:44,510
Is it someone I know?

469
00:30:52,120 --> 00:30:53,120
Oh, Dad!

470
00:30:59,860 --> 00:31:00,900
Honey.

471
00:31:03,470 --> 00:31:05,130
I thought you weren't coming home.

472
00:31:05,970 --> 00:31:07,600
Of course, I'd come.

473
00:31:09,940 --> 00:31:11,240
I'm home.

474
00:31:15,310 --> 00:31:18,150
Honey... What happened?

475
00:31:30,590 --> 00:31:33,030
It's all here. Thank goodness.

476
00:31:33,100 --> 00:31:34,400
I'm saved.

477
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:38,900
- I took the store items back.
- Good.

478
00:31:40,340 --> 00:31:43,410
I was so worried! I was afraid
you'd go gambling again...

479
00:31:43,470 --> 00:31:44,670
Let's get a divorce.

480
00:31:45,310 --> 00:31:47,340
- What?
- I said, let's get a divorce.

481
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:50,380
What do you mean, a divorce?
What matters is that you're back.

482
00:31:50,450 --> 00:31:51,780
You can clean up your act,
and we'll be fine.

483
00:31:52,050 --> 00:31:54,380
I no longer want to live with you,
Yang Dong Suk.

484
00:31:54,380 --> 00:31:57,250
What? You're the one in the wrong.
What right do you have to be angry?

485
00:31:57,320 --> 00:32:00,620
I really hate you.
I can't even stand to look at you.

486
00:32:02,890 --> 00:32:03,890
What?

487
00:32:05,090 --> 00:32:06,100
Why?

488
00:32:08,560 --> 00:32:10,100
Why did you stop loving me?

489
00:32:10,670 --> 00:32:12,340
It's not that I stopped loving you.

490
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:18,010
I never loved you
in the first place.

491
00:32:18,980 --> 00:32:19,980
From the beginning?

492
00:32:21,610 --> 00:32:25,920
But, then...
Then, why did you marry me?

493
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:29,990
You were dependable,
like a big brother,

494
00:32:30,390 --> 00:32:33,390
and like a good person. And...

495
00:32:36,160 --> 00:32:39,100
You come from a family of doctors,
so I thought I would be well-off.

496
00:32:41,100 --> 00:32:42,170
Thanks.

497
00:32:43,330 --> 00:32:44,930
Thanks for being so honest.

498
00:32:46,300 --> 00:32:48,240
And if I'm being brutally honest,

499
00:32:48,740 --> 00:32:50,510
I never even wanted to have a child.

500
00:32:53,510 --> 00:32:55,080
Wow, it feels good
to get that off my chest.

501
00:32:56,580 --> 00:32:59,680
So I was the only one in love
this whole time, and I had no idea?

502
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:04,020
Wow. You must have been
miserable living with me.

503
00:33:05,150 --> 00:33:06,660
That's not it...

504
00:33:06,990 --> 00:33:10,960
I ran away because I couldn't
stand seeing you get hurt.

505
00:33:11,030 --> 00:33:12,030
Let's do it.

506
00:33:13,600 --> 00:33:14,600
Let's get a divorce.

507
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:30,350
- I am not divorcing you.
- Yes, you are.

508
00:33:30,680 --> 00:33:32,250
If you don't, I'll run away again.

509
00:33:32,420 --> 00:33:35,320
If you hate me that much,
at least stay for Ji Hu.

510
00:33:35,420 --> 00:33:39,020
Ji Hu's all grown up.
He knows what's going on.

511
00:33:39,260 --> 00:33:43,090
I'll explain things to Ji Hu.
Let's just end this amicably.

512
00:33:43,460 --> 00:33:45,230
I will never agree to a divorce.

513
00:33:45,560 --> 00:33:48,700
If my father or my brother
finds out, they'll go ballistic!

514
00:33:48,770 --> 00:33:50,530
That's so ridiculous.

515
00:33:50,530 --> 00:33:52,540
Your mom, your ex, and
your sister-in-law have all left!

516
00:33:52,600 --> 00:33:54,540
So why can't I?

517
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:56,740
Please, stop.

518
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:00,640
I won't ask you to be nice to me.

519
00:34:01,180 --> 00:34:03,710
It was so hard for me
after my mom left.

520
00:34:04,310 --> 00:34:07,480
Hyun Bin and Eun Bin, too.
After their mom left,

521
00:34:07,520 --> 00:34:09,450
they had such a hard time
growing up.

522
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:13,520
Please, let's not do that
to our Ji Hu. Honey, please?

523
00:34:14,920 --> 00:34:16,560
I'll do better, I promise. Okay?

524
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:30,270
(Taehan)

525
00:34:32,610 --> 00:34:34,710
Ms. Gong! Over here!

526
00:34:37,050 --> 00:34:38,480
Gosh, you scared me.

527
00:34:41,450 --> 00:34:43,890
Ms. Gong,
has it been a few hours already?

528
00:34:44,590 --> 00:34:45,790
About five.

529
00:34:46,760 --> 00:34:50,160
So why are you eating dinner here
instead of going home?

530
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:55,130
I have no family waiting up for me,
and my fridge is empty.

531
00:34:55,430 --> 00:34:58,730
I lost track of time
while outlining my presentation.

532
00:34:59,300 --> 00:35:03,340
But I'm glad. I get to have dinner
with you, Ms. Gong.

533
00:35:05,480 --> 00:35:08,980
Ms. Gong, would you want to go
on a blind date with my brother?

534
00:35:09,880 --> 00:35:10,950
A blind date?

535
00:35:15,250 --> 00:35:17,520
Where did that come from?

536
00:35:17,820 --> 00:35:21,260
He's handsome, fit, and easygoing.
And he makes tons of money.

537
00:35:21,320 --> 00:35:23,260
He's the total package.

538
00:35:23,790 --> 00:35:25,330
For a second, I thought
you were talking about me.

539
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:30,100
- You're laughing too loud.
- My bad.

540
00:35:31,730 --> 00:35:34,840
Ms. Gong, please marry my brother.

541
00:35:34,900 --> 00:35:37,440
Please, be a part of my family!

542
00:35:38,310 --> 00:35:41,110
Forget it.
I'm not thinking about marriage.

543
00:35:41,210 --> 00:35:45,880
- Come on, Ms. Gong.
- Let's just eat. All right?

544
00:35:46,550 --> 00:35:47,550
Okay.

545
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:49,750
Hey, by the way...

546
00:35:50,090 --> 00:35:52,820
- Are you two working late tonight?
- Yes. Why?

547
00:35:53,420 --> 00:35:56,860
You must've missed the notice.
There's a facility check at 8 p.m.

548
00:35:56,960 --> 00:35:57,990
They're shutting off the heat.

549
00:36:03,100 --> 00:36:06,500
Are there any meeting rooms
we can book?

550
00:36:10,140 --> 00:36:12,310
None? Okay, got it.

551
00:36:14,110 --> 00:36:16,910
Oh, they're all booked?
All right, I understand.

552
00:36:18,310 --> 00:36:21,680
What should we do?
All the co-working spaces are full.

553
00:36:22,620 --> 00:36:23,920
Now, what?

554
00:36:24,820 --> 00:36:28,220
- Should we try a hotel?
- What?

555
00:36:28,220 --> 00:36:30,790
Why? There's one right next door.

556
00:36:31,660 --> 00:36:32,900
Right, exactly.

557
00:36:33,530 --> 00:36:36,870
It's right next door,
so tons of people will see us,

558
00:36:37,470 --> 00:36:39,500
and they might get the wrong idea,
don't you think?

559
00:36:40,300 --> 00:36:42,040
We're just friends.

560
00:36:44,670 --> 00:36:46,180
I know, but still...

561
00:36:48,280 --> 00:36:49,750
Maybe we could...

562
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:52,350
go to my place?

563
00:37:05,030 --> 00:37:08,060
You take this white sundae gopchang,
wrap it in a perilla leaf...

564
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:09,830
It'll blow your mind.

565
00:37:10,630 --> 00:37:14,200
I absolutely love sundae gopchang.
How did you know?

566
00:37:15,370 --> 00:37:16,970
Because you've always loved it.

567
00:37:18,740 --> 00:37:19,740
That's right.

568
00:37:21,180 --> 00:37:24,280
I threw in some plain sundae too,
on the house.

569
00:37:25,550 --> 00:37:28,680
It's nice you have company for once.
You always come alone.

570
00:37:30,020 --> 00:37:31,020
Your girlfriend?

571
00:37:32,020 --> 00:37:34,920
Gosh, no. We're just...

572
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:37,460
Friends. Old friends.

573
00:37:37,830 --> 00:37:40,430
Oh, my mistake.

574
00:37:41,630 --> 00:37:44,470
- Thanks so much. Have a good night.
- You too. Come again.

575
00:37:44,530 --> 00:37:45,740
- We will.
- Take care.

576
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,770
Yes, I just got home.

577
00:37:51,770 --> 00:37:54,310
Did you narrow down the candidates
for the model?

578
00:37:54,580 --> 00:37:56,510
Instead of an actor or a celebrity,

579
00:37:56,780 --> 00:37:59,080
we're looking for a prominent figure
who hasn't been in ads or shoots.

580
00:37:59,720 --> 00:38:03,350
But in that case,
won't they be completely unknown?

581
00:38:03,850 --> 00:38:07,590
But it's a win-win since they'd fit
the premium image we're going for.

582
00:38:08,190 --> 00:38:11,560
Do you know Dr. Han Seong Mi?
She's a psychiatrist on TV shows.

583
00:38:11,630 --> 00:38:13,460
Who did you say?

584
00:38:13,860 --> 00:38:15,530
Wow, you've already got
everything set up.

585
00:38:15,770 --> 00:38:19,140
What was that?
Hey, is that Gong Ju Ah with you?

586
00:38:19,740 --> 00:38:22,540
What are you two doing together
at your place this late?

587
00:38:22,610 --> 00:38:25,340
- We're just friends, that's all!
- Give me a break! Hey!

588
00:38:25,710 --> 00:38:28,140
My gosh! Did he just hang up on me?

589
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:29,910
"Friends," my foot.

590
00:38:32,980 --> 00:38:34,020
What are you going to do?

591
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:36,820
I'll just face some grilling,
that's all.

592
00:38:37,290 --> 00:38:38,290
Come on, let's eat.

593
00:38:42,490 --> 00:38:44,830
I have a feeling it'll be more
than just "some grilling."

594
00:38:45,930 --> 00:38:49,030
We'll deal with that later.
Let's eat first.

595
00:38:50,230 --> 00:38:52,440
Okay, let's dig in.

596
00:38:53,140 --> 00:38:54,540
Okay, the sundae first.

597
00:38:58,910 --> 00:39:03,280
- This plump sundae and...
- And the chewy tripe. Great combo.

598
00:39:05,510 --> 00:39:09,220
You have some too, Director.
Oh, should I make a wrap for you?

599
00:39:10,050 --> 00:39:14,620
Okay, so some sundae and tripe.

600
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:15,960
Some onion.

601
00:39:16,360 --> 00:39:20,130
- Add onion and a hot pepper? Good?
- I'm okay.

602
00:39:20,630 --> 00:39:21,630
And then...

603
00:39:23,330 --> 00:39:24,330
Open wide.

604
00:39:24,870 --> 00:39:26,970
Hey, I made this wrap just for you.

605
00:39:27,270 --> 00:39:29,610
- Open wide. Come on.
- No, I'm good.

606
00:39:31,370 --> 00:39:34,610
- Fine...
- There you go. Delicious, isn't it?

607
00:39:37,950 --> 00:39:38,950
Delicious, right?

608
00:39:40,980 --> 00:39:42,050
All right, then...

609
00:39:46,060 --> 00:39:47,790
The rice cakes!
I have to eat the rice cakes, too.

610
00:39:55,630 --> 00:39:58,500
What is it? Am I stuffing my face?

611
00:40:01,270 --> 00:40:04,740
Didn't I always say
you have a healthy appetite?

612
00:40:05,640 --> 00:40:07,340
I don't really remember
you saying that.

613
00:40:10,380 --> 00:40:13,250
Right. About the model
for FG's premium line,

614
00:40:13,580 --> 00:40:15,450
they're considering
Dr. Han Seong Mi.

615
00:40:16,090 --> 00:40:17,090
What?

616
00:40:17,950 --> 00:40:19,160
The people at work...

617
00:40:19,420 --> 00:40:22,020
don't know that Dr. Han is
your mother, do they?

618
00:40:22,490 --> 00:40:26,360
Right. At work, Mr. Park
is the only one who knows.

619
00:40:27,160 --> 00:40:28,160
You don't like the idea?

620
00:40:31,130 --> 00:40:32,800
My mom will probably turn it down.

621
00:40:33,300 --> 00:40:35,470
She absolutely hates
that I'm a designer.

622
00:40:37,010 --> 00:40:41,310
She's still mad I quit medicine
when I already had my license.

623
00:40:43,610 --> 00:40:45,650
So I'm the reason your relationship
with your mother went sour.

624
00:40:46,620 --> 00:40:47,620
If I...

625
00:40:47,880 --> 00:40:50,020
hadn't opened up
that new world for you,

626
00:40:50,350 --> 00:40:51,850
you would've become a doctor, right?

627
00:40:53,460 --> 00:40:56,590
I shouldn't have said anything!
Now, I totally regret it.

628
00:40:57,190 --> 00:40:58,190
Seriously.

629
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,230
By the way,

630
00:41:02,630 --> 00:41:04,430
why aren't you interested
in getting married?

631
00:41:07,340 --> 00:41:10,640
Well... There's no big reason.

632
00:41:10,970 --> 00:41:15,240
It's just that I don't know
any happily married people.

633
00:41:18,980 --> 00:41:19,980
Director.

634
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:22,890
Do you remember my uncle?

635
00:41:24,020 --> 00:41:27,160
Of course, I remember Uncle Dae Han.
He was always so good to me.

636
00:41:28,960 --> 00:41:31,860
He's been going through
a really tough time lately.

637
00:41:32,700 --> 00:41:33,700
Why? What's wrong?

638
00:41:37,030 --> 00:41:39,540
His wife had an affair and left him.

639
00:41:41,870 --> 00:41:42,970
My gosh.

640
00:41:43,610 --> 00:41:45,410
Is there something in the water
in Onjeong?

641
00:41:45,470 --> 00:41:50,250
- Right? Why is everyone leaving?
- Unbelievable.

642
00:41:51,810 --> 00:41:53,480
The one she had the affair with...

643
00:41:53,480 --> 00:41:55,250
can't be someone
in my family, right?

644
00:41:56,050 --> 00:41:59,420
Of course not!
Don't even say something so awful.

645
00:42:00,160 --> 00:42:01,820
Gosh, I take it back.

646
00:42:02,120 --> 00:42:03,860
Now that I've said it out loud,
that does sound horrible.

647
00:42:04,660 --> 00:42:06,900
Go away, bad juju! Go away!

648
00:42:07,260 --> 00:42:08,260
What are you doing?

649
00:42:08,330 --> 00:42:13,040
Don't jinx it! We can't repeat
that nightmare from 30 years ago.

650
00:42:13,840 --> 00:42:17,810
For me, too. Go away, bad thoughts.
Go away! Goodness.

651
00:42:18,570 --> 00:42:20,510
And this sundae also needs to...

652
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:22,280
disappear into my mouth.

653
00:42:26,450 --> 00:42:28,680
So, he agreed to the divorce?

654
00:42:29,820 --> 00:42:30,890
That's great.

655
00:42:32,150 --> 00:42:34,460
Things are a little messy on my end.

656
00:42:35,460 --> 00:42:39,760
Hey, don't worry.
I want a clean slate with you, too.

657
00:42:40,830 --> 00:42:43,100
Yes, I'll take care of it
by tomorrow, no matter what.

658
00:42:43,670 --> 00:42:46,100
Yes. All right, sleep well.

659
00:42:46,370 --> 00:42:47,370
Got it.

660
00:42:50,410 --> 00:42:52,170
Do I have to get on my knees
and beg her?

661
00:42:52,940 --> 00:42:54,340
Seriously... Darn it.

662
00:42:57,150 --> 00:42:59,150
Darn it!

663
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:11,960
So that's why
that jerk wanted a divorce.

664
00:43:12,860 --> 00:43:14,200
What are you going to do?

665
00:43:14,960 --> 00:43:17,270
Are you going to divorce him?

666
00:43:19,400 --> 00:43:20,640
I can't.

667
00:43:21,640 --> 00:43:22,970
I can't divorce him.

668
00:43:25,070 --> 00:43:26,080
I see.

669
00:43:26,810 --> 00:43:29,680
If you're not going to divorce him,
then there's only one thing to do.

670
00:43:31,250 --> 00:43:33,480
We have to find out who she is
and make her pay.

671
00:43:35,420 --> 00:43:38,920
Dong Suk.
You need to listen to me carefully.

672
00:43:41,920 --> 00:43:44,730
Dae Han,
please listen to me carefully.

673
00:43:45,660 --> 00:43:46,800
Okay.

674
00:43:47,630 --> 00:43:51,900
This only happened because
your wife made an immature choice.

675
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:54,540
It's not your fault at all.

676
00:43:56,070 --> 00:43:58,040
So please, don't blame yourself.

677
00:43:58,670 --> 00:43:59,980
Let's focus on helping you recover.

678
00:44:00,710 --> 00:44:03,510
But how can I not?
The whole family's worried about me.

679
00:44:04,750 --> 00:44:06,320
I'm really okay, though.

680
00:44:06,650 --> 00:44:10,450
It's okay not to be okay, Dae Han.
We're family.

681
00:44:12,890 --> 00:44:13,890
So...

682
00:44:14,190 --> 00:44:16,860
don't just force a smile
and pretend you're okay.

683
00:44:17,430 --> 00:44:19,460
All your pent-up,
painful feelings...

684
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:22,700
Don't hold them in. Let it all out.

685
00:44:23,370 --> 00:44:24,370
Okay?

686
00:44:26,470 --> 00:44:27,470
Okay.

687
00:44:40,420 --> 00:44:41,620
What are you doing in my room?

688
00:44:42,620 --> 00:44:43,620
Were you waiting for me?

689
00:44:44,650 --> 00:44:47,260
Waiting? No. I just couldn't sleep.

690
00:44:47,790 --> 00:44:50,290
I was looking for some sheet music
and thought it might be in here.

691
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:53,560
What sheet music?
You mean Dad's old yellow songbook?

692
00:44:54,560 --> 00:44:56,500
I bundled all that up
and put it in storage.

693
00:44:56,800 --> 00:44:57,830
You did? I see.

694
00:44:58,870 --> 00:45:02,870
How about we sing one from memory?
Mom's favorite.

695
00:45:02,970 --> 00:45:05,540
- "I Miss You More and More."
- Right, that one!

696
00:45:06,710 --> 00:45:08,810
Is this the right key for it?

697
00:45:10,510 --> 00:45:11,810
Yes, that's it.

698
00:45:13,450 --> 00:45:17,120
<i>My darling love, once so kind</i>

699
00:45:17,490 --> 00:45:19,990
<i>Have you forgotten me?</i>

700
00:45:21,120 --> 00:45:26,560
<i>Have you already forgotten me?</i>

701
00:45:30,170 --> 00:45:31,470
Hey, did you hear about Hui Gyeong?

702
00:45:31,870 --> 00:45:32,870
What?

703
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:37,440
- Yes, I heard.
- Man...

704
00:45:38,940 --> 00:45:41,210
Gosh, I feel so bad for Seong Mi.

705
00:45:41,710 --> 00:45:44,450
If I had moved out,
she could be using this room by now.

706
00:45:45,210 --> 00:45:48,350
Don't be silly.
I like sharing a room with my wife.

707
00:45:50,190 --> 00:45:51,190
So I get the credit for that?

708
00:45:52,220 --> 00:45:55,090
Wow, thanks a lot. Really.

709
00:45:55,860 --> 00:45:57,130
Sing it. Come on.

710
00:46:02,970 --> 00:46:08,370
<i>Have you forgotten me,</i>
<i>leaving me to long for you?</i>

711
00:46:09,940 --> 00:46:15,080
<i>- Have you already forgotten me?</i>
<i>- Have you already forgotten me?</i>

712
00:46:18,080 --> 00:46:21,080
Goodness. Why are they singing?
People are trying to sleep.

713
00:46:22,550 --> 00:46:25,290
I told him to go comfort him,
and now look at them.

714
00:46:26,090 --> 00:46:27,860
That's your favorite song, isn't it?

715
00:46:28,490 --> 00:46:31,960
Dad used to sing that for you too,
back in the day.

716
00:46:34,130 --> 00:46:36,830
They say sad things happen to people
who like sad songs.

717
00:46:36,830 --> 00:46:38,930
Now, I wonder
if these things keep happening...

718
00:46:38,930 --> 00:46:40,470
because I like sad songs.

719
00:46:41,570 --> 00:46:45,340
You're taking on too much
by blaming yourself for everything.

720
00:46:46,240 --> 00:46:49,240
How can everything that's gone wrong
possibly be your fault?

721
00:46:51,050 --> 00:46:52,920
Oh, Mother.

722
00:46:53,980 --> 00:46:56,820
My poor, heartbroken mother-in-law.

723
00:46:57,490 --> 00:46:58,990
I'm going to have to prescribe you
a dose of love.

724
00:47:03,430 --> 00:47:05,130
We're going to be okay.

725
00:47:06,600 --> 00:47:08,260
We'll be fine, Mother.

726
00:47:10,400 --> 00:47:14,970
<i>- I never knew</i>
<i>- I never knew</i>

727
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:18,310
<i>- That your heart</i>
<i>- That your heart would change</i>

728
00:47:19,840 --> 00:47:22,980
<i>I really never knew</i>

729
00:47:42,560 --> 00:47:44,730
Gosh, I swear...

730
00:48:24,510 --> 00:48:25,510
Are you awake?

731
00:48:26,910 --> 00:48:28,180
I wasn't asleep.

732
00:48:30,650 --> 00:48:32,480
You say that,
but you were dead to the world.

733
00:48:33,080 --> 00:48:35,050
What would you have done
if you'd taken a cab by yourself?

734
00:48:36,350 --> 00:48:40,460
Why turn on the seat warmer?
I got cozy and fell asleep.

735
00:48:44,560 --> 00:48:45,560
Thanks for today.

736
00:48:48,330 --> 00:48:49,670
I'll be going in tomorrow, too.

737
00:48:50,530 --> 00:48:53,800
- Should I pick you up tomorrow?
- No, that's okay.

738
00:48:54,440 --> 00:48:56,000
You should go get some rest.

739
00:48:56,870 --> 00:48:57,870
All right.

740
00:48:59,680 --> 00:49:01,210
Thanks for the ride home, Director.

741
00:49:12,120 --> 00:49:14,520
I'll wait up,
so can you text me when you're home?

742
00:49:14,820 --> 00:49:15,860
I'll just end up worrying.

743
00:49:16,690 --> 00:49:18,890
- Okay.
- Go on.

744
00:49:33,810 --> 00:49:36,240
Gosh, I don't want to be
just friends.

745
00:49:37,150 --> 00:49:38,150
What am I going to do?

746
00:49:43,620 --> 00:49:44,620
Mom, are you crazy?

747
00:49:45,320 --> 00:49:47,290
She stole that money.
You'll give it to her as alimony?

748
00:49:47,560 --> 00:49:50,360
I have my reasons.
Just leave it at that.

749
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:54,460
So you moved out of your apartment
just to do them a favor.

750
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:56,400
It's just money.
I can always make more.

751
00:49:58,370 --> 00:50:00,400
About the model
for FG's premium line,

752
00:50:00,400 --> 00:50:02,470
they're considering
Dr. Han Seong Mi.

753
00:50:04,670 --> 00:50:08,740
Mom, are all the clothes you wear
for your TV appearances sponsored?

754
00:50:10,110 --> 00:50:12,980
It's mostly my own stuff.
Sponsored clothes are a pain.

755
00:50:13,750 --> 00:50:15,920
Your fees can't be high enough
to justify buying new outfits.

756
00:50:16,280 --> 00:50:18,050
Don't start with me
this early in the morning.

757
00:50:20,020 --> 00:50:21,120
I'm heading out.

758
00:50:22,590 --> 00:50:23,990
You came home so late last night.

759
00:50:23,990 --> 00:50:25,190
It's the weekend.
Where are you going?

760
00:50:25,490 --> 00:50:26,700
I'm going to work.

761
00:50:27,130 --> 00:50:30,300
And here I was thinking
you'd finally gotten a boyfriend.

762
00:50:30,430 --> 00:50:33,100
Oh, please. After what happened
with Uncle? Dating?

763
00:50:33,200 --> 00:50:37,970
I've lost all interest. Bring me
the most amazing guy in the world,

764
00:50:38,040 --> 00:50:39,070
and I wouldn't even blink.

765
00:50:40,710 --> 00:50:41,710
Gosh, that brat...

766
00:51:16,580 --> 00:51:17,580
Gong...

767
00:51:32,560 --> 00:51:33,560
Hey, So Hye.

768
00:51:33,830 --> 00:51:35,530
Oh? Ms. Gong.

769
00:51:35,900 --> 00:51:38,330
Is that your boyfriend, So Hye?
He's handsome.

770
00:51:40,870 --> 00:51:42,840
What do you think? Not bad, right?

771
00:51:43,210 --> 00:51:46,110
Yes, you guys look great together.
He's cute.

772
00:51:46,410 --> 00:51:48,640
If you think he's cute,
I can set you up.

773
00:51:49,010 --> 00:51:50,350
He's actually my older brother.

774
00:51:50,910 --> 00:51:53,620
Oh, the total package?

775
00:51:53,720 --> 00:51:57,650
Yes! You should be my sister-in-law,
Ms. Gong!

776
00:51:58,750 --> 00:52:00,420
I've told you I'm not interested
in getting married.

777
00:52:00,590 --> 00:52:04,260
That's only because
you haven't met the right guy yet.

778
00:52:05,130 --> 00:52:06,130
You think so?

779
00:52:07,400 --> 00:52:08,460
Good morning.

780
00:52:09,700 --> 00:52:11,570
- Good morning, Director.
- Morning.

781
00:52:11,630 --> 00:52:15,100
- Good morning.
- Hi. Ms. Kim, why are you here?

782
00:52:15,170 --> 00:52:16,240
You should be taking
the weekend off.

783
00:52:17,310 --> 00:52:20,210
Okay, I'll talk to my brother
and get right back to you.

784
00:52:20,680 --> 00:52:22,140
Is that all right?

785
00:52:22,680 --> 00:52:25,880
Gosh, this is awkward.
I already said no, thank you.

786
00:52:26,480 --> 00:52:27,650
Anyway, let's just head inside.

787
00:52:27,980 --> 00:52:28,980
Okay.

788
00:52:36,890 --> 00:52:38,260
You're trying to set me up again?

789
00:52:39,160 --> 00:52:42,360
Gosh, So Hye.
Why are you being so pushy?

790
00:52:42,630 --> 00:52:44,270
I'm telling you,
I'm really not interested.

791
00:52:44,900 --> 00:52:49,000
Fine, okay.
Just one cup of tea. That's it.

792
00:52:49,540 --> 00:52:50,540
Tea? Why?

793
00:52:50,970 --> 00:52:52,510
Let's just meet somewhere close by.

794
00:52:53,140 --> 00:52:55,580
What about the hotel coffee shop
right next to the office?

795
00:52:56,780 --> 00:52:57,810
Yes.

796
00:52:57,810 --> 00:52:59,950
(Taehan Group)

797
00:53:12,860 --> 00:53:15,360
It's chrysanthemum tea, Father.
Caffeine-free.

798
00:53:15,660 --> 00:53:16,670
All right.

799
00:53:17,630 --> 00:53:18,630
Father?

800
00:53:19,030 --> 00:53:22,600
I want to return the 40,000 dollars
you transferred to me.

801
00:53:23,340 --> 00:53:24,340
Why?

802
00:53:24,510 --> 00:53:27,740
I originally asked because
I had a pressing need for it,

803
00:53:27,910 --> 00:53:29,440
but that's no longer the case.

804
00:53:29,910 --> 00:53:33,010
Keep it anyway.
Buy yourself something nice.

805
00:53:33,210 --> 00:53:36,820
No, Father. You always give me
more than I need.

806
00:53:37,550 --> 00:53:42,060
And as for my husband...
Please give him time to cool off.

807
00:53:42,220 --> 00:53:43,220
He'll come around soon.

808
00:53:45,290 --> 00:53:46,290
All right.

809
00:53:51,500 --> 00:53:54,740
That thing you said before
about settling Hyun Bin down...

810
00:53:55,070 --> 00:53:56,140
What's the status on that?

811
00:53:56,840 --> 00:53:59,910
Oh, I was
just about to bring that up.

812
00:54:00,540 --> 00:54:04,350
Councilor Hwang has a daughter
who's more than ready to marry.

813
00:54:04,710 --> 00:54:05,710
Really?

814
00:54:05,910 --> 00:54:07,450
Starting tomorrow,

815
00:54:07,450 --> 00:54:09,050
I'll get close to the Councilor
and his wife at golf.

816
00:54:09,150 --> 00:54:12,720
Then I'll set up their daughter
with our Hyun Bin.

817
00:54:14,560 --> 00:54:15,790
You really do...

818
00:54:17,160 --> 00:54:19,760
have a plan for everything.

819
00:54:23,800 --> 00:54:26,430
(70s and 80s Throwback Concert)

820
00:54:31,970 --> 00:54:32,970
Hey.

821
00:54:40,720 --> 00:54:44,450
I left a printout of the proposal
on your desk for you to review.

822
00:54:44,890 --> 00:54:46,350
I'm heading out for the day.

823
00:54:48,560 --> 00:54:51,860
Wait, she's just going to leave
for her blind date like that?

824
00:54:54,900 --> 00:54:59,200
(Hotel)

825
00:55:16,150 --> 00:55:17,620
Why did I even follow her here?

826
00:55:18,390 --> 00:55:20,560
What do I care
if she goes on a blind date?

827
00:55:21,120 --> 00:55:22,120
We're just friends.

828
00:55:54,290 --> 00:55:56,190
- Director?
- What?

829
00:55:57,560 --> 00:55:59,990
You got my text, right?

830
00:56:00,300 --> 00:56:01,300
Yes.

831
00:56:02,500 --> 00:56:04,230
You said you were leaving,
but you're here?

832
00:56:04,970 --> 00:56:07,600
I was just picking up some sweets
for my uncle.

833
00:56:07,900 --> 00:56:10,040
Wow, this cake sells out so fast,
you know?

834
00:56:10,270 --> 00:56:13,270
Luckily, I was able to
get the last one.

835
00:56:13,780 --> 00:56:17,010
Actually, it's sold out every time,
so I missed out last time too.

836
00:56:17,080 --> 00:56:19,810
I assumed I'd be out of luck again
today,

837
00:56:20,150 --> 00:56:22,180
which makes finally getting one
feel even better.

838
00:56:23,420 --> 00:56:27,960
My uncle can be surprisingly picky.
I hope he likes it.

839
00:56:28,320 --> 00:56:30,760
If he hates it, too bad.
He'll just have to like it, right?

840
00:56:33,460 --> 00:56:35,760
By the way,
what brings you here, Director?

841
00:56:37,700 --> 00:56:38,730
I was just wondering that myself.

842
00:56:39,230 --> 00:56:40,840
Why am I here, indeed?

843
00:56:42,670 --> 00:56:45,410
Didn't you say you were stepping out
to buy something?

844
00:56:45,870 --> 00:56:47,940
What did you need from here?

845
00:56:56,450 --> 00:56:58,450
(Police)

846
00:56:59,920 --> 00:57:02,820
(Onjeong Police Substation)

847
00:57:03,390 --> 00:57:06,030
Why do you think it's so quiet?

848
00:57:06,330 --> 00:57:07,500
Tell me about it.

849
00:57:08,060 --> 00:57:10,530
It's eerily quiet,
like the eye of a storm.

850
00:57:11,700 --> 00:57:14,900
We can't tell anyone
what we know, right?

851
00:57:15,270 --> 00:57:16,400
Of course not.

852
00:57:16,840 --> 00:57:19,110
As far as anyone's concerned,
we don't know anything.

853
00:57:19,570 --> 00:57:22,610
But what if
both families find out...

854
00:57:23,040 --> 00:57:24,250
That's only a matter of time, right?

855
00:57:24,580 --> 00:57:26,880
And then a tornado's going to hit.

856
00:57:26,950 --> 00:57:28,580
(Onjeong Police Substation)

857
00:57:28,650 --> 00:57:30,650
We could be looking at
the storm of the century.

858
00:57:31,190 --> 00:57:32,290
Officer Jung.

859
00:57:32,820 --> 00:57:35,060
It's our job to stop it.

860
00:57:35,620 --> 00:57:39,730
It seems the peace of Onjeong
rests in our hands.

861
00:57:42,300 --> 00:57:43,300
Yes, sir.

862
00:57:43,930 --> 00:57:46,730
We're on high alert.
Let's start our patrol.

863
00:57:47,600 --> 00:57:48,600
Let's do it.

864
00:57:48,670 --> 00:57:51,570
(Onjeong Police Substation)

865
00:57:56,180 --> 00:57:58,610
Dong Suk, please listen to me.

866
00:57:58,750 --> 00:58:01,380
If we're going to live like this,
maybe it's better if we...

867
00:58:08,320 --> 00:58:09,620
Ta-da!

868
00:58:10,630 --> 00:58:14,600
- We match. Do you like them?
- What?

869
00:58:15,560 --> 00:58:17,230
Yes. You guys look great.

870
00:58:17,930 --> 00:58:19,830
I got a new outfit
for the special occasion.

871
00:58:20,400 --> 00:58:22,400
So, how was your business trip?

872
00:58:22,670 --> 00:58:23,670
Sorry?

873
00:58:24,410 --> 00:58:26,270
Yes, of course.

874
00:58:26,810 --> 00:58:29,310
And here I thought you'd run off
with the family silver.

875
00:58:30,280 --> 00:58:32,580
Honey, don't be ridiculous.
As if he'd do that.

876
00:58:33,210 --> 00:58:34,780
And you, what's with the long face?

877
00:58:36,890 --> 00:58:40,460
Dong Ik, if I were really
that kind of person,

878
00:58:41,360 --> 00:58:45,590
- we'd have to divorce, right?
- Divorce? What are you saying?

879
00:58:46,360 --> 00:58:48,360
The word "divorce" is forbidden
in this house.

880
00:58:48,800 --> 00:58:53,430
If anything like that happens,
you'll leave this house in a casket.

881
00:58:54,140 --> 00:58:55,370
Honey, please.

882
00:58:56,540 --> 00:58:57,610
My gosh.

883
00:58:59,140 --> 00:59:00,170
Yes, ma'am?

884
00:59:01,580 --> 00:59:04,080
What do you mean by that?

885
00:59:06,110 --> 00:59:08,550
Mr. Hwang canceled his tee time?

886
00:59:10,050 --> 00:59:11,490
What? All of a sudden?

887
00:59:11,890 --> 00:59:14,920
Wait, can you at least tell me why?
Hello?

888
00:59:16,260 --> 00:59:17,330
Did they hang up?

889
00:59:18,430 --> 00:59:19,430
Yes.

890
00:59:20,360 --> 00:59:22,430
I'm sure that jerk Jeong Han
is behind this.

891
00:59:22,830 --> 00:59:25,800
I told you.
He'd try to take everything from me.

892
00:59:27,740 --> 00:59:28,940
That jerk...

893
00:59:30,200 --> 00:59:31,570
Yes, sir.

894
00:59:32,270 --> 00:59:35,980
I'm calling about the petition
against the night market you signed.

895
00:59:36,240 --> 00:59:37,980
I just wanted
to talk to you about...

896
00:59:38,780 --> 00:59:39,780
Pardon?

897
00:59:42,050 --> 00:59:43,890
So you haven't signed it yet.

898
00:59:44,490 --> 00:59:48,220
Yes, it seems I was misinformed.
My apologies.

899
00:59:50,120 --> 00:59:53,860
Gosh, that jerk. I knew it.
I can't believe that Bucket.

900
00:59:53,930 --> 00:59:55,060
Hey, Gong Jeong Han!

901
00:59:57,100 --> 00:59:58,930
Speak of the devil.

902
00:59:59,930 --> 01:00:01,300
You jerk. Explain yourself.

903
01:00:01,700 --> 01:00:04,240
- What did you do?
- What did I do?

904
01:00:04,610 --> 01:00:07,640
You're the one in the wrong.
How dare you come at me first?

905
01:00:07,740 --> 01:00:09,180
Why did you meet
with Councilor Hwang?

906
01:00:09,610 --> 01:00:12,980
What did you say that made him
cancel the golf outing?

907
01:00:14,150 --> 01:00:18,390
What are you talking about?
Change my mind? How could I?

908
01:00:20,250 --> 01:00:22,990
If we try to run away,
they'll chase us forever.

909
01:00:23,690 --> 01:00:25,860
Let's get a clean divorce
and start over fresh, okay?

910
01:00:26,760 --> 01:00:29,560
Okay, fine. But let's meet,
even if it's just for a moment.

911
01:00:29,560 --> 01:00:32,400
All right, I'll meet you there.
Okay.

912
01:00:33,070 --> 01:00:36,300
Dong Suk, listen carefully
to what I'm about to say.

913
01:00:37,610 --> 01:00:39,040
They say if you know your enemy
and know yourself,

914
01:00:39,340 --> 01:00:40,980
you can win a hundred battles.

915
01:00:41,540 --> 01:00:44,680
If we're going to nail her, we need
to know who she is, don't we?

916
01:01:17,810 --> 01:01:22,120
Did you want to say something to me?
Is that why you gave me a ride?

917
01:01:23,180 --> 01:01:25,150
I was just gathering my thoughts
on the way.

918
01:01:26,420 --> 01:01:29,290
What is it that's so serious?
You're making me nervous.

919
01:01:30,020 --> 01:01:31,190
Earlier today,

920
01:01:31,990 --> 01:01:34,160
I didn't go to the hotel
on business.

921
01:01:34,660 --> 01:01:35,930
I thought...

922
01:01:36,060 --> 01:01:38,070
you were on your blind date,
so I followed you.

923
01:01:39,670 --> 01:01:41,570
My blind date is tomorrow.

924
01:01:44,240 --> 01:01:45,270
That's a relief.

925
01:01:46,270 --> 01:01:48,680
If that had been your date today,

926
01:01:49,780 --> 01:01:52,010
I probably would've crashed it.

927
01:01:54,080 --> 01:01:55,120
Why?

928
01:01:57,020 --> 01:01:58,090
Because I would've hated it.

929
01:02:02,060 --> 01:02:03,520
The thought of you smiling...

930
01:02:04,390 --> 01:02:07,660
at another guy like that...
I just couldn't stand it.

931
01:02:09,630 --> 01:02:10,670
But we're...

932
01:02:11,270 --> 01:02:12,500
just friends.

933
01:02:13,670 --> 01:02:15,070
I know.

934
01:02:16,100 --> 01:02:18,970
My head knows that, but my heart...

935
01:02:19,340 --> 01:02:22,880
- My gosh.
- Surprised? Yes, me too.

936
01:02:22,940 --> 01:02:24,750
- Auntie?
- Auntie?

937
01:02:35,660 --> 01:02:38,630
- What is she doing here?
- Hui Gyeong.

938
01:02:39,990 --> 01:02:41,460
- Hui Gyeong.
- Oh, hi!

939
01:02:41,700 --> 01:02:42,700
Uncle?

940
01:02:43,730 --> 01:02:44,730
He's your uncle?

941
01:02:49,270 --> 01:02:50,270
- My gosh.
- Oh, gosh!

942
01:02:50,870 --> 01:02:52,310
What is going on? What's with them?

943
01:02:52,910 --> 01:02:54,340
I have no idea.

944
01:02:58,850 --> 01:03:01,620
My gosh, what's wrong with them?
What's their deal?

945
01:03:04,290 --> 01:03:06,420
- What? What's going on?
- Auntie.

946
01:03:07,290 --> 01:03:08,290
What?

947
01:03:50,160 --> 01:03:53,070
(Recipe For Love)

948
01:03:53,130 --> 01:03:54,600
- You lost the election...
- One, two, three.

949
01:03:54,670 --> 01:03:56,470
- because people don't like you.
- Do this!

950
01:03:56,470 --> 01:03:59,870
It's a complete misunderstanding.
Someone is trying to frame me.

951
01:04:00,210 --> 01:04:03,840
- So only Dad and Uncle don't know?
- Right.

952
01:04:03,910 --> 01:04:06,050
Goodness gracious.
You really scared me.

953
01:04:06,110 --> 01:04:08,350
I saw my uncle near home.

954
01:04:09,850 --> 01:04:10,890
Oh, my.

955
01:04:12,250 --> 01:04:14,090
Don't you ever contact
that woman again.

956
01:04:14,220 --> 01:04:16,720
- I swear I'll do better.
- You made the right decision.

957
01:04:16,920 --> 01:04:19,290
- Get your act together from now on.
- I will.

958
01:04:20,730 --> 01:04:23,130
I really hope it goes well.

959
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:24,930
(Yang Dong Ik to the rescue!)

960
01:04:25,000 --> 01:04:27,870
Do you know who your wife
is having an affair with?
